STEPS TO RUN ANY QUERY FOR PROJECTS ON JOERN CONSOLE


CASE 1: YOU NEED TO LOAD A WHOLE PROJECT INTO JOERN CONSOLE AND OBTAIN A JSON FILE WITH ALL FUNCTIONS OF THE PROJECT. 

1. Open Joern console by opening your terminal on the path where the project you want to analyse is located. 
2. Replace the name of the folder containing the project, example for RIOT project: 
Command: joern> importCode("RIOT-master") 
3. Enter following query 
Command: joern> cpg.method.where(_.columnNumber).whereNot(_.name("<global>")).map(m=>(m.name, m.callee.whereNot(_.name("<operator>.*")).l.size,m.start.dump)).toJsonPretty |> "callperfunc_riot.json" 

CASE 2 : YOU NEED TO FIND THE NUMBER OF EXTERNAL CALLS IN A PROJECT 

1. Command: 
joern> cpg.method.callee.filter(_.isExternal == true).whereNot(_.name("<operator>.*")).l.size 

CASE 3: YOU NEED TO FIND THE NUMBER OF INTERNAL CALLS IN A PROJECT 

1.Command: 
joern> cpg.method.callee.filter(_.isExternal == false).whereNot(_.name("<operator>.*")).l.size 

CASE 4: YOU NEED TO FIND THE NUMBER OF FUNCTION DEFINITIONS 

1. Command 
joern> cpg.method.where(_.columnNumber).whereNot(_.name("<global>")).l.size   
